Just a larger version of the map.
Made because it was too small and I was hoping 
the server I play on would pick up map.  The nades
are hyped and do mad damage, so a small map would be campfest
nade fest.  

It takes a long time to compile the first run in a botmatch.
I have included the .nav file in hopes that it helps run on
server, or you don't have to do wait for compile.

I have found putting it to 640x480 and low res on textures 
speeds compiling.  Took me 3 tries before it worked so be
patient.  It crashes right at end,  so CTL ALT DEL and look
to see if it has stopped responding,  it will crash out anyways.
See the splash page image and you're good.

I set the bots to zero, and then walk to middle of map and then use the
sv_cheats_1    and then
nav_generate   to run it instead of letting it run from bot match start.

This is the best version I came up with.  It plays fun.
I love the sprays of dust kicking up all over the place,
it also helps see your aim.

I will try a new map now,  I am done with this.

I have included the editor maps as well so people can
mod this.  I tried to use the shaded lighting,  but I swear
there is not one good lighting primer I could find,  and
the trees were all white when I put one in there,  so do it
yourself if you want fancy lighting. Sorry I am not pro.

Oh put .bsp and .nav into the maps file.  include the other files if you want to edit it.

This has all stock textures and sprites so it will easily run on server
with no extra crap.   I don't know if you could use it on a Gun Game server.
It is set up like a normal death match.   If you want to mod it to run on Gun Game server then fine.  Like I said,  I don't have any idea what the difference in the programming for gun game would be,  if any.  

This was the final version of the map,  or test map package that I put up.
chupong2sky5fix2  was about the name in it.  Golden trees was a add on package that I had a hell of a time making work when I reinstalled game.
So I erased them and made it all stock!!

There is a terrorist buyzone; however, to add realism terrorists must make
their way about a block up the road from their spawn to a gun shop where
they can buy weapons.  Don't get mad though, the terrorists have plenty
of guns already in their hide-out, but each weapon only has one clip.

Map Specialties - 2 cars that explode when shot with a high enough powered weapon, a bus with a bomb on board that explodes when the detonator is pushed (its in a building nearby), police cars, a rotating bar sign, new civilian vehicles from the Insurgency Mod for HL2, a generator that emits sparks after it is shot, a working camera in the security booth and many custom textures.

You should now be able to play on it.

	C:\...\Steam\steamapp\**username**\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps\kb_cataclysm_testbox_v1.bsp

Hey guys this is my new map, "bc_ghostpipes". It is a small snow map with many hills and mounds to climb on or you can go down low to attack for some CQB action. There is also the "ghost pipe" as I like to call it, which is invisible to the naked eye until you are inside it. You can swim through it to get to the other side of the map.

UPDATE: 3:56 P.M. 2/4/2012:
I added some walls, adjusted the lighting, and reduced the amount of ghost pipes to only 1 ghost pipe. You can find it behind 2 half-buried crates in each spawn.
_______________________________

Please have fun, and give me feedback on what you want me to add or remove from this map! 

Thanks for everyone who sees this page.

A bricked in warehouse full of boxes, navigate the maze
of tetris shaped box configurations and... well shoot
the opposite team.

The entire floor is made of floorboards, so you can hear
the enemy coming, lots of pinch points and sniper points
but all points have ways around.

Recommended settings for server, leave footsteps on as
this map would be a bitch in utter silence from the
foot department.


- DevoiD
